@Comment:	Chi. 20 winthrop street hyde park M.A. 11;3.91 to my best cousind Kathy Hribar when you get here I will savelots of candies for you and me and don't forget your Baby Brother John paul. thank you and when you come you could hold our hammsters. thenk you againe
@Comment:	MOT gets Chi started with some suggestions and is very formal about where to write the return address and date; Mot coaches a lot about how capital letters are used , etc; once the heading is finished , Chi works independently , stopping a few times to ask for spelling; so most of the main text was Chi's idea; at end Mot explains that if something is misspelled she (Kathy) won't understand what she (Chi) is trying to say!; Mot ends up doing reading back of letter
